inn1.comm: comes over the wicket and he sprays it so wide outside off that it beats everybody, creeps past first slip's legs

first blood to West Indies, Powell lands it on a good length and gets it to shape away sharply from the left hander, Butt lunges forward to push it to the off side and the outside edge travels comfortably to Findlay at second slip, Butt committed himself to the stroke too early
bang on target, lands it outside off and hits the deck hard, Younis taps it back to the bowler
gets a bit of gentle swing from the region of the off stump, he safely sees it through

just holds the length back a bit and gets it to come back in, he pushes it towards short cover and sets off for a quick single, Manzoor really had to sprint to the other end, the under arm flick was just wide of the stumps
hits a good length outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching Marshall
switches to a much fuller length, he gets well forward and pushes it down to mid-off
more like a warm up delivery, lands on a full length outside off and moves away slightly, that's a tester for Marshall who dives to his right to pouch it
left alone outside off, not much bounce, easily handled by Marshall
switches to a good length, he plays it with an angle and steers it towards point
gets forward and drives a fullish delivery angling away from him, Chattergoon at short cover fumbles and that's a bonus for Younis
full outside off again and he pushes it to the off side
drives to mid-off on the walk and the fielder mistimes his dive and the ball lobs off his body and rolls towards mid-on
just a fraction wide outside off and he opens the face of the bat and angles it wide of backward point
gets a just a bit more pace on that and hits a good length, cramps him for room so he has to settle for a defensive push back to the bowler
holds the length back and shapes away slightly, well kept by Marshall
squares him up around the off stump and Manzoor fails to cover the line properly, he gets an outside edge but it bounces in front of second slip
gets good bounce and pace outside that off stump, he shows good judgement in letting it go
tucks him up again with a bit of extra bounce but he gets back and across and taps it in front of his stumps, thinks of a cheeky single but Younis wasn't interested by any means
gets it to angle away from around the middle stump, he gets across the line and pushes it to the off side
hits a good length on middle and leg, he gets behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler
false shot from Younis, he stays rooted to the crease and tries to cut but the extra swing beats him
another superb away swinger and he backs it up with pace too, he tries to drive and the outside edge wasnt too far away
pitches on off and middle, he pushes it to the off side
flicks his wrists and works it down to short mid-on and a ,misfield prompts a single, Younis was off in a flash but Manzoor was very circumspect, he eventually makes his ground
chops it to the off side and they take off quickly, the fielding isn't up to the mark
Dropped That really should have been taken, Manzoor gets forward and plays a square drive on the up and Miller at point seemed to have it all covered, he grabs at it and the ball slips away
pushed down to the off side
gets forward and drives on the up back to the bowler
overpitches on middle and leg, he shows the full face of the bat and punches it really hard on the front foot, the ball shoots past the bowler, Manzoor and beats mid-on comfortably
tries to work it through the on side but is squared up by the extra bounce
full outside off, he gets well forward and defends to the off side
swings towards the pads, he gets his wrists working and clips it to midwicket
gets it to swing away late and he covers the line and drives firmly to cover
pitches on middle and leg and clips his pads just outside the line of the leg stump, he appeals but withdraws
slides on the pads and he waits for the ball to come to him and flicks it late, the timing is good enough to beat midwicket but the ball slows before reaching the boundary
lands on a good length on middle and leg, he turns his wrists and pushes it back to the bowler
hits a good length outside off, he drives through the line and beats cover for a couple
short and wide, invitation to cut and he obliges, he stays at the crease and carves it wide of backward point
lands outside off and comes back in after pitching, he safely shoulders arms
this one bounces just a touch more but he plays it with soft hands and fends it to the off side
angles towards the pads, he works it to the on side
pitches on off and middle, he tries to work it to the on side but plays it back to the bowler
pushes it back down the pitch
full outside off, he opens the face of the bat and steers it to the off side
hits a good length outside off, he gets behind the line and pushes it to the off side
hits a good length and gets it to shape away, he works it to point
hits the deck hard outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching Marshall
this was much wider, he chooses not to play a stroke and watchfully sees it through to the keeper
gets his front foot across his stumps and safely shoulders arms again
bowls the first yorker of the day, he manages to dig it out easily outside the off stump
gets it to angle across the right hander and he shuffles and calls for two runs as soon as he flicks it wide of square leg

Dropped: It's Marshall this time, it was a superb delivery, pitches on the corridor outside off and Manzoor just had to play at it, Marshall gets behind the ball, fails to hang on, juggles and puts it down, a regular keeper would have taken that
short and inviting the pull, he pulls way too early and the ball only meets his glove
pitches outside off, there's good bounce and carry to Marshall
switches to a fuller length, he gets well forward and works it wide of slip and down to third man
he's cramped for room as he tries to cut and nearly trudges on to his stumps, the ball rolls to cover
hits a good length outside off, he pushes it to the off side
just a touch wide outside off, he angles it down to third man
hits a good length outside off, he shuffles back and chops it towards point
gets it to angle inwards and he works it towards midwicket and thinks of a single
holds the length back for some extra bounce, he goes on the hop and chops it to the off side
the slower ball foxes him as he tries to slam that past backward point, he's not moving his feet much
angles towards the pads, he uses his wrists well and flicks it wide of square leg, the boundaries are pushed back and that allows three runs
bangs the bouncer but directs it wide down the leg side
fuller in length and angled towards the pads, he works it just wide of mid-on and sets off
full and straight outside the off stump, he gets forward to cover the line and drives to mid-off
strays on the pads and he flicks it to mid-on with a gentle flick of the wrists
just a touch too wide outside off and he dabs it away gently down to third man
holds the length back outside the off stump, he rocks back and cuts it down to sweeper cover
drifts on the pads, he moves across the stumps a touch and flicks it to deep square leg
full and swinging away outside off, he gets forward and drives to cover who dives and cuts it off
pitches on a full length and Manzoor gets well forward and drives firmly back to the bowler on the 'V'
a little slower in pace, he softly nudges it to square leg
slower ball, misdirects it wide of the off stump
delivers from slightly wide of the crease and pitches it around the off stump, he gets across and taps it to the on side
just strays wide down the leg side and it nearly clips his pads as he tries to work it down to fine leg
the slower ball and he picks it well, he lunges forward to the full delivery and forcefully works it wide of mid-on, he maintains his balance and pushes it with power
angled towards the pads again but this time it's fielded on the on side
wide outside off but the ball doesn't bounce much, he shapes to cut and the outside edge races to third man, Sarwan does well to slide and mop up
pitches outside off, he works it to the on side
hits a good length on middle and off, he tucks it to deep square leg
the slower ball pitches wide outside off, he cuts to backward point
gets it to skid through on middle and leg, he works it to the on side
pushes this one towards midwicket and almost takes the single for granted, Younis wasn't even looking at his partner, Manzoor smiles when he realises that there was no run in the first place
hits a good length outside off, he steers it to the off side
waits for it outside the off stump, he opens the face of the bat and steers it wide of backward point
gets it to cut back in to the right hander sharply but he adjusts well by playing it with an angled bat down towards gully
gets the angle across the right hander but this is fuller in length, he pushes it to Findlay at short cover
walks across his stumps before delivery and pushes a full ball straight to Findlay at short cover, he's been alert in that position
slightly wide of the off stump, he opens the face of the bat and steers it to third man
full and in the slot to drive, he mistimes it and pushes it tamely to mid-off
precision and placement, lovely shot, he gets behind the line to a very full delivery and pushes it back past the bowler very firmly, mid-on had no chance, that's the 50 stand as well
opens the face of the bat and angles it down to third man
similar delivery, there's a big gap past backward point and he opens the face of the bat and picks up a single
full and pushed back past the bowler firmly, there's protection at mid-on to cut it off
makes use of the movement off the pitch, opens the face of the bat and angles it past the vacant slips and down to third man, it was a little premeditated
short of a good length on middle and leg, slower through the air, worked away towards square leg
tossed up on middle and leg, pushed to mid wicket
tossed up on middle and off this time, defended
flatter on middle and leg, swept uppishly to deep square leg
back of a length outside off, spinning away, cut to short third-man
flighted outside off, pushed wide of point for a comfortable single
tossed up outside off, gets outside the line and works it towards square leg
gave it some air outside off again, fuller, driven to long on
short of a good length outside off, played firmly off the back foot to deep cover
short of a good length outside off, tries to cut, misses
tossed up, pitches short of a good length outside off, delicately cut away wide of short third man for a couple
flighted on middle and off, driven to long on
flighted outside off, he commits to the forward push and beats Miller
not quite in the length to cut but he improvises by making room and slicing it wide of backward point
flighted on middle and leg, he pushes it to the off side
gives it a lot of air outside off, he gets on his knee and fetches it
flighted outside off, he pushes it to the off side
slightly shorter in length, he makes room and slices it to sweeper cover
floated on the pads, he works it to the on side
gives him a bit of width outside off, he makes room and cuts to sweeper cover to bring up his fifty
flighted on middle and leg, pushes it to the on side
gets forward and chips it uppishly towards mid-on
flighted on middle and leg, he pushes it to the on side
full on middle, he pushes it wide of mid-on
shuffles and tries to work it to the on side and the ball appears to clip his pad in front of leg stump, they appeal but the umpire shakes his head
plays it to the off side
pushed to the on side, he takes a quick single
opens the face of the bat and deliberately dabs it wide of the keeper
stays on the back foot and pushes it towards cover
gets back and across and pushes it back to the bowler
gets forward to a flighted delivery and works it to midwicket
short outside off, Gayle gets a bit of extra bounce, Manzoor attempts to slash it on the up down towards third man but can't beat Nash, he dives forward at short third man and takes it easily
tries to cut very close to the body and the ball trickles past the keeper, they take a run and Misbah is struggling
chips it on the up to short midwicket
slides down the leg side
good length outside off, he makes room and takes a single to the off side
gets forward to a flighted delivery on middle and off and pushes it to midwicket
flighted outside off, he pushes it to sweeper cover
gets across his stumps and turns it to short midwicket
flighted outside off, defended back to the bowler
gets forward and pushes a full delivery to mid-off
Appeal the ball skids through low as he tries to work it to the on side, the ball hits his pad in front of the stump but there appeared to be 2 noises, inside edge i reckon
pushed to long on
flighted on middle and leg, pushed to long on
makes room outside off and cuts to third man
flighted on middle and leg, he works it to mid-on
flighted on middle and leg, he works it wide of square leg
stays back to a ball which keeps low, he pats it away safely
flighted on middle and leg, he works it behind square on the on side
good length outside off, makes room and cuts to the off side
flighted on middle and leg, he pushes it back to Miller
gets across his stumps and tucks it to the on side
slower through the air, he softly nudges it to midwicket
flighted on middle and leg, he nudges it to square leg
flighted on middle and leg, he commits to the sweep early and plays it with force past square leg, he finds the gap easily
pushed back to the bowler
pushed back to the bowler
down the leg side, difficult one for Marshall
flighted on middle and off, pushed back to gayle
flighted on off, defended on the front foot
gets on his knee early for the sweep but fails to make contact with the bat
pushed back to the bowler
short and wide, he makes room and cuts down to deep cover
angles it on middle and leg, he pushes it to the on side
flighted outside off, he pushes it towards long-off
gets his front foot across the stumps and fetches it from outside off to fine leg
drives firmly down the ground and beats Miller who dives and fails to get a hand to it
flighted outside off, he places it back to the bowler
wide outside off, hardly any turn, he makes room and cuts to the offside
stays back at the crease an hits it through the line to long-on
gets across his stumps and tucks it behind square on the on side
gets on his knee early and plays a premeditated paddle down to fine leg
flighted on middle and leg, he pushes it to the on side
gives it a lot of air on middle and leg, he sees the flight, gets on his knee and slog sweeps it high over square leg, the placement is spot on
pitches outside off, doesn't exert himself much, he waits on it before dabbing it down to third man
hits a good length outside off and the ball holds its line, he gets back and pushes it back to the bowler
short and wide, he gets his bat high above his shoulders and carves it down to third man, the recoil is quite amusing to watch, if you've seen Younis bat
cramps him for room to cut, he steers it to point
well bowled again, he tries to squeeze it past the off side but can't beat the gap
good length delivery outside off, Misbah pushes it to point and again can't find the gap
outside off, pushes it to cover for a single
punches it to deep cover for a single
short in length outside the off stump, cuts it to third man for a single
fuller outside off, pushes it to cover
fuller in length outside the off stump, Younis comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
outside the off stump, Misbah steers it away to third man for a single
outside the off stump, gets back and punches it to cover
fuller on the middle stump and coming in, Younis moves across and lofts it high over long on for a huge six
fuller in length on the middle stump, Younis pushes it to mid-on and runs across for a quick single
outside the off stump, Misbah steers it to third man for a single
short outside the off stump, slices it to third man for a single
on the leg stump, flicks it to deep midwicket
driven away to deep cover
slider outside the off stump, Misbah moves back and pushes it to short fine leg
tossed up and pushes it to long-on
on the leg stump, comes forward and pushes it to short fine leg
works it away to deep midwicket
comes forward and drives it to sweeper cover for a single
full toss on the leg stump, turns it to midwicket
good length delivery, hoicks it to deep midwicket for a couple
on the leg stump and full, Malik pushes it to long-on
fuller on the leg stump, pushes it to deep midwicket
outside the off stump, drives it back to the bowler, who misfields and costs the team a single
outside the off stump, goes for hoick and gets an inside edge onto his pads
